<br>
I’ve done some research and a lot of searches on this Forum and I have found a lot of great information on the Skald class, their abilities, their specialties, and their limitations.  I’m looking into creating a Sklad and I still have a few questions that I cannot find answers to.  I am currently a lvl 50 Infiltrator – R5L7 and have been playing since release so I have a very good understanding of the game in general, but my questions fo you are specific to a class I have limited knowledge about.  Mid/Bedevere is VERY empty, so I run into Skalds very rarely.<br>
<br>
First, let me give a brief background on what I will be doing with my Skald; I will mainly be a BG Skald, most likely grouping with a Pac Healer and Supp Spiritmaster.  I am either going to create a Troll, Norse or Dwarf – but, I am unsure which I would be better off creating... thus, bringing me to my first question:  How much does Dex effect the life of a Skald.  I’m aware that Dex does not effect weapon skill for Skalds as Sword, Axe, and Hammer are based 100% on Str… so what, if any, role does Dex play?<br>
<br>
Trolls have much greater Str than Dwarves, but dwarves have greater Con and Dex and Quickness, and Norse are in between.  Will the reduced Quick and Dex of the Troll play a roll in anything except swing speed?  I’m aware greater Quick = faster swing speed and reduced dmg, but is that all it effects for the Sklad?<br>
<br>
Second question, my BG3 Skald spec is; 33 BS, 25 Weapon, 9 Parry.  However, I have yet to settle in on a weapon choice.  I certainly want the highest speed and the most weapon dmg I can manage – I believe the best cut of is 25 weapon while maintaining 33 BS for Speed.  I could gain 1 more point in Weapon spec and lose 6 parry, but I don’t think it’s worth it.<br>
<br>
Axe, Sword, and Hammer all seem to have similar styles 2-25.  All have; Parry moves at 4, anytime styles at 10, and combo moves off 10 at 18 and 25.  The only real difference at this level being minor discrepancies in; to hit bonus, endurance, and def penalty effects.  I’m aware of the Armor tables for Hib/Alb – crush being + to plate etc.  I’m leaning more toward Sword or Hammer at this time, due to the defensive penalties in lower level Axe styles.  Does this sound logical or am I reading the style spreadsheets wrong?  (http://home.nc.rr.com/obsidianguard/wyrd/Midgard.htm)<br>
<br>
I think those are my two main questions at this time.  To sum up real fast; Troll v Norse v Dwarf – Str v Con/Quick and Sword v Hammer.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time – I’d appreciate any helpful comments and suggestions you have on these topics.  Feel free to suggest a different build and even some RA’s if you wish.<br>
