<br>
Weapon- right now swords are bugged, they do piss poor damage and the styles are pathetic.  Axe and Hammer are mixed in advantage/disadvantage.  Axe has some good properties in that all Alb classes are neutral to slash so you wont be seeing any minuses from that.  Hammer is great against the tank and friar tanks that you will be fighting.  Infiltrators will own you so it doesnt really matter which one you take.<br>
<br>
Spec- If you want speed and buffs for bg, go with the songs.  That is really the best approach.  Also, as everyone else in bg will most likely be twinks, expect to hook up with an armorer/scer.  At the bg level the damage variance can be minimized by boosting your weapon skill with crafted items.  <br>
<br>
Race-  Trolls do amazing front end damage.  That strength really plays arole there.  Dex influences your parry rate.  Not that you are going to parry.  Humans and kobolds are also viable options, with kobies haveing a slight size advantage.  But, as someone commented, they would make a small human.  The extra con will play more of a role in which to take than the str/dex issue.  This will give you more hitpoints to keep the infi in step for one more round so your realmates can avenge your death much easier.  Unless, of course, you get a mez off first.  But that is highly unlikely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kortzdymundskyn>Kortz Dymundskyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/1/03 7:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=596.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skalds</span><hr size=1> Being a dwarf skald, Ill put up my answers here.<br>
<br>
I enjoy the dwarf because it gives a good size of toon, plus the Con score is rather nice. Since all our weapon choices are built on Strength, it doesnt matter which weapon you use in the overall scheme of things.<br>
<br>
But that leads to my next answer. I have broken down the 3 Midgard weapons like this:<br>
Axe: Fast swing times, lowest damage<br>
Sword: Average swing time and damage<br>
Hammer: Slowest swing time, highest damage<br>
<br>
If you are going to use weapon and board, I would do a sword or axe skill. If you will be 2 handed, like most skalds I see, I would do either axe or hammer.<br>
<br>
This is from a mostly best number type of thinking. I went 2 hand sword, and havent regretted it since... <p>Bays Endruhms<br>
